<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-04-28T12:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-04-28T12:36:00-05:00" n="1083" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1083">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.11/3908.</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Vera Cruz</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-04-28T11:00:00-06:36">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 28, 1914, 11 a.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>One of my messengers has just returned with following message from
                            federal General Maas, now at Soledad: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Consul</hi>: I hereby answer your
                                    esteemed letter of the 25th instant, advising that in accord
                                    with instructions which I have received from my Government the
                                    military authorities of the jurisdiction under my command have
                                    been ordered to permit foreigners of any nationality whatsoever
                                    to leave the Republic at will.</p>
                                <p>Relative to Mexican citizens who desire to leave the city at Vera
                                    Cruz you may permit or prohibit same according to the orders you
                                    may have in the premises.</p>
                                <p>I am [etc]</p>
                                <p rend="right">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">G. Maas</hi>.</p>
                            </quote>
                        </p>
                        <p>This communication is dated Soledad de Doblado, April 27.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Canada</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>